<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list stagger">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is my data really private?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Yes. High Vibes is built from the ground up for local-first privacy:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>No network requests</strong> — your prompts and responses never leave your machine during inference.</li>
            <li><strong>No telemetry</strong> — we collect zero usage data, crash reports, or analytics.</li>
            <li><strong>Local model execution</strong> — models run on your hardware via Ollama, LM Studio, or llama.cpp.</li>
            <li><strong>Local storage only</strong> — conversations and settings are stored in plain files on your disk.</li>
            <li><strong>Open-source &amp; auditable</strong> — every line of code is public. You can verify these claims yourself.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><a href="/privacy/" class="faq-link">Read our full privacy architecture →</a></p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can High Vibes access my files?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Only when you explicitly grant access. High Vibes can integrate with your file system for context-aware assistance, but every file access requires your permission through the system's native file picker or a directory you configure. No background scanning or indexing occurs without your consent.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is the code auditable?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Fully. High Vibes is open source under a permissive license. You can inspect every line of code on <a href="https://github.com/high-vibes-io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>, build from source, and verify that no data leaves your machine. We encourage security researchers and privacy advocates to audit the codebase.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What models can I use?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Any model supported by Ollama, LM Studio, or llama.cpp — including Llama 3, Mistral, Phi-3, Gemma, and hundreds more. Premium users can also access cloud models like GPT-4 and Claude as a fallback.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What hardware do I need?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>A modern Mac (M1+), Linux, or Windows machine with at least 8GB RAM. Smaller models like Phi-3 run well on modest hardware; larger models benefit from 16GB+ and a discrete GPU.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is it really free?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>The core product is free and open source, forever. Premium adds optional cloud model access, advanced automations, and priority support for a monthly fee.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How is this different from ChatGPT/Claude?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Those are cloud services — your data goes to their servers. High Vibes runs locally on your machine, integrates with your existing tools, and gives you full control over which models you use.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

